    <chapter id="Compiling">
      <title>Compiling the ADG library</title>

      <section id="Requirements">
        <title>Requirements</title>
        <para>
        The ADG library is strongly based on the GObject framework (included inside
        the GLib abstraction layer) and uses Cairo as rendering engine. Both the
        libraries are required.
        </para>

        <variablelist>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://www.gtk.org/">GLib</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>[required] 2.10.1 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
	<term><ulink url="http://sourceforge.net/projects/gcontainer/">GContainer</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>[required] 1.99.2 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://cairographics.org/">Cairo</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>[required] 1.6.0 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://www.gtk.org/">Gtk+2</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>[optional] 2.8.0 or later, in order to compile the demonstration programs</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        </variablelist>
      </section>
    </chapter>
  </part>

